DEEKS:
Callen?

36:17.542 --> 36:18.909
Sam!

36:20.845 --> 36:22.646
(grunting)

36:36.494 --> 36:38.628
(car alarm wailing)

36:38.663 --> 36:40.664
Son of a bitch.

36:42.667 --> 36:44.968
KENSI (muffled):
Guys, you okay?

36:45.003 --> 36:47.837
Here, I got you.

36:47.872 --> 36:49.472
You okay?
You all right?
Yeah.

36:49.507 --> 36:51.541
Think so.

37:07.892 --> 37:10.460
I need a drink.

37:10.495 --> 37:12.695
(sniffles)

37:12.730 --> 37:15.665
(exhales)

37:15.700 --> 37:18.768
Mr. Beale, come on.
You're gonna pour.

37:24.709 --> 37:26.710
(mouths)

37:27.712 --> 37:29.713
Thanks.

37:33.651 --> 37:35.418
Hey.

37:35.453 --> 37:38.821
So, Michelle's body
was recovered by LAPD.

37:38.856 --> 37:40.790
Uh, they found it in a van

37:40.825 --> 37:43.893
left where the tour bus
was hijacked.

37:43.928 --> 37:46.496
They're personally escorting it
to the morgue now.

37:46.531 --> 37:48.331
Callen's taking Sam there.

37:48.366 --> 37:49.766
Good. Okay.
Yeah.

37:49.801 --> 37:51.567
Um...
Yeah.

37:51.602 --> 37:53.336
...and Sabatino?

37:53.371 --> 37:55.505
Sam cuffed him
in an alleyway.

37:55.540 --> 37:57.540
Maybe that's an oops.
I-I don't...

37:57.575 --> 37:59.008
Ooh.
Yeah.

37:59.043 --> 38:02.545
Well, he probably escaped,
I mean, he's good at that stuff.

38:02.580 --> 38:04.013
Yeah.

38:04.048 --> 38:06.683
Anything else? Are you okay?

38:07.719 --> 38:09.552
No.

38:09.587 --> 38:12.422
I just...

38:12.457 --> 38:15.625
I feel so badly for Sam.

38:15.660 --> 38:18.295
I can't imagine losing someone
that close to you.

38:22.667 --> 38:25.468
Came through straight around
here, we cut him off.

38:27.505 --> 38:30.106
Neither can I.

38:30.141 --> 38:32.675
Um, will you excuse me
for a second?

38:32.710 --> 38:34.010
Course.

38:35.413 --> 38:36.612
Hey, Tony?

38:36.647 --> 38:37.714
Yeah.

38:37.749 --> 38:38.915
Can I borrow that flashbang?

38:38.950 --> 38:40.583
Uh, yeah, I guess.

38:40.618 --> 38:41.785
What for?

38:42.820 --> 38:45.021
Surprise.

38:49.694 --> 38:51.728
Banging.

38:51.763 --> 38:53.596
Deeks, can I talk to you
for a sec?

38:53.631 --> 38:55.365
Yeah.

38:55.400 --> 38:56.766
The hell was that?

38:56.801 --> 38:59.102
Um, a, um...
(clears throat)

38:59.137 --> 39:00.770
Sorry, could you just
give me a hand.

39:00.805 --> 39:01.805
What?

39:03.574 --> 39:05.408
Whoa, no.
Martin Deeks, will you marry me?

39:05.443 --> 39:06.676
No, no, co-- baby,
you got to stand up.

39:06.711 --> 39:08.411
No, Deeks, no.
Get up, get up...

39:08.446 --> 39:10.980
Listen, you can't. You can't,
you can't, you can't do this.

39:11.015 --> 39:12.115
Deeks, I think I just did.

39:12.150 --> 39:13.850
No, but you can't,
because, y-you...

39:13.885 --> 39:16.686
the guy, the guy has to,
the guy has to propose.

39:16.721 --> 39:19.122
Oh, really?
'Cause I think it's 2017.

39:19.157 --> 39:21.391
And you kind of had your shot.

39:21.426 --> 39:23.493
Not to be a stickler for detail,

39:23.528 --> 39:25.061
but I've actually proposed
three times,

39:25.096 --> 39:27.163
if you count
the very romantic version I did

39:27.198 --> 39:28.564
while you were in a coma.

39:28.599 --> 39:31.768
Baby, what are
you doing?

39:31.803 --> 39:34.771
¶ These dreams
we're holding... ¶

39:34.806 --> 39:37.740
Life is really short, Deeks.

39:37.775 --> 39:40.643
I mean, we saw that today,
and we see it every day.

39:40.678 --> 39:43.646
¶ All the world is
ours to take... ¶

39:43.681 --> 39:46.115
And I don't know how much time
either one of us has left,

39:46.150 --> 39:48.885
but I do know this:

39:48.920 --> 39:52.755
I want to spend the rest
of what I have with you.

